{"type":"message","id":"472f9389","parentId":"aedcfe42","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:19:23.278Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_808f79d9-2385-42cd-946a-11ff4d228b91","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 11:35 UTC / 13:35 SAST — Pre-compaction flush\n\nUser: Increased context window to 100k. First, update my memories with this conversation. Change nothing else. I am assuming I will need to restart the gateway, yes?\n\nMe:  \n- Understood. Waiting for explicit yes before acting.  \n- User confirmed: increase context window to 100k.  \n- User assumes gateway restart needed.  \n- Next step: backup config, then update openclaw.json → set contextWindow: 100000 for nemotron-3-super:cloud  \n- Then restart gateway (user to confirm when ready)  \n- No other changes.  \n- Memories updated only in memory/2026-03-25.md (this file).\n## Session Summary (2026-03-25)\n- User analyzed communication patterns: direct/task-focused with both Dawn (MiniMax) and Nemotron (me)\n- Initial Nemotron responses: overly detailed (\"walls of text\") — user disliked\n- User feedback: prefer brief, consecutive sentences; ask if unsure instead of guessing\n- User confirmed I used session-logs skill correctly to read jsonl files\n- Config change applied: nemotron-3-super:cloud contextWindow → 100000, agents.defaults.model.primary → ollama/nemotron-3-super:cloud\n- No backup made (per user request)\n- Gateway restart pending (user to handle)\n\n\n## 12:09 UTC / 14:09 SAST — Sprint Check-in\n- Project: Research NavaAA/NavaSM/gap analysis tool setup  \n- Status: Research complete, notes taken, plan devised  \n- Next: await user instruction to proceed with implementation  \n- Blockers: none  \n\n\n## 16:01 UTC / 18:01 SAST — Heartbeat\n- TrnsBank: 62 lines, well under 200 cap, no action needed\n- Tiny switched back to minimax (from nemotron)\n- Tiny asked: Nemotron summary + readiness for Yosef meeting\n- I asked what the Yosef meeting is about — no reply yet\n- Sprint check-in deferred — Tiny's last message was ~27 min ago, in inactive window\n- Next action: await Tiny's response on Yosef meeting context\n\n\n## Pre-compaction Memory Flush — 2026-03-25 14:03 UTC\n\n### Durable Memories to Preserve\n\n**Workflow State (Nava Content System):**  \n- NavaAA agent processed topic: \"Nava Healthcare recruitment fee model\"  \n- Completed prerequisite checks:  \n  - Multiple session status checks  \n  - Gateway restart executed  \n  - Configuration file reviewed (openclaw.json)  \n  - Memory and transcript bank reviewed  \n  - Context window verified at 100k for nemotron-3-super:cloud  \n  - Primary model set to ollama/nemotron-3-super:cloud  \n- Agent paused at human review gate — awaiting Approve/Challenge/Refine signal via WhatsApp  \n\n**System Status:**  \n- WhatsApp gateway: Disconnected (status 428) → Reconnected  \n- Sprint check-in triggered:  \n  - Checking TrnsBank.md for messages  \n  - If messages exist: wait for user to lock bank before analysis  \n  - If ≥200 messages: analyse immediately  \n  - Next: update memory/2026-03-25.md and commit to git  \n\n**Context Preserved:**  \n- NavaAA agent is ready to generate LinkedIn post after prerequisite validation  \n- Human-in-the-loop workflow active at review gate  \n- All NavaSM agent/skill preparations complete (created earlier)  \n- Gap analysis tool enhanced with RAG semantic search  \n- Testing workflow planned for end-to-end validation  \n- Setup and handoff documented in NAVA_SETUP.md  \n\n### Note on Transience  \n- Session-specific details (pids, exact timestamps, transient tool calls) not stored here  \n- Only durable decisions, completed workflow steps, and system states preserved  \n- Raw session logs remain in `~/.openclaw/agents/navaaa/sessions/` for forensic review  \n\n\n## Sprint Check-in (20:03 SAST)\n\n**Session status:**\n- TUI session active (20:03 SAST)\n- WhatsApp gateway unstable today (disconnecting/reconnecting every ~60s since 18:35)\n- Model: