eated isolated AWAA agent (awaa-agent) ready for use\n- Added utility scripts for agent creation and corpus examination\n- Skill integrates with existing 77-article AbroadWorks corpus in rag_abroadworks/clean_md/\n\n**Files Created**:\n- awaa-system-prompt.md (14,781 bytes) - Complete agent instructions\n- SKILL.md (14,046 bytes) - Skill documentation and usage guide\n- README.md (2,802 bytes) - Quick start reference\n- Scripts: awaa.sh (agent creation), check-corpus.sh (corpus analysis)\n\n**Verification**:\n- AWAA agent successfully spawned and visible in openclaw agents list\n- All skill files properly formatted and executable\n- Follows same patterns as existing nava-writing skill for consistency\n\n**Next Steps**:\n- Users can create AWAA agents with: ./awaa.sh \"[topic]\"\n- Interact via openclaw message send --target awaa-agent -m 'You are AWAA. [task]'\n- Follow 5-phase workflow for article creation\n- Use ./check-corpus.sh to explore available topics\n\n**Related Work**:\n- Builds on Nava article writing methodology adapted for AbroadWorks context\n- Ready for immediate use in creating AbroadWorks blog articles following editorial SOPs\n\n\n## Sprint Check-in (20:03 SAST)\n\n**TrnsBank:** 161 messages — under threshold, no analysis needed\n\n**Active work:**\n- AWAA article draft 1 saved to drafts folder + backup\n- Humanizer workflow initiated — awaiting Tiny's decision on tool/approach\n\n**Next action:** Wait for Tiny to decide on humanizer process, then apply to draft and compare differences.\n\n## Sprint Check-in (00:03 SAST — Mar 27)\n\n**TrnsBank:** 161 messages — under 200 threshold, waiting for Tiny to lock bank before analysis\n\n**Project status (Mar 26 session):**\n- AWAA Drafts 3, 4, 5 complete — Draft 5 saved to docs/AbroadWorksContent/drafts/\n- Editor skill created with all writing rules + common errors\n- Resource maps updated (MEMORY.md, TOOLS.md)\n- Backup: ~/TinyBackUp/20260326/\n- Committed: Yes\n\n**Next:** Nava LinkedIn + X work (Mar 