{"type":"message","id":"6562f5b4","parentId":"85664569","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:00:13.961Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_77b60f8e-2b0b-4b61-8502-5ae199887312","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## TinyQE Progress (2026-03-28)\n\nBuilt strategic brief, framework, and working prototype for TinyQE content evaluation tool:\n\n### What's Complete\n- **Strategic Brief**: `tinyqe/TinyQE_Nemotron_Brief.md` - defines TinyQE purpose, 12-dimension model, format profiles, output design, anti-patterns\n- **Implementation Framework**: `tinyqe/TinyQE_Nemotron_Framework.md` - technical blueprint with architecture, module specs, scoring logic, file structure\n- **Working Prototype**: 7/12 analyzers implemented with full pipeline:\n  - ✅ A1: Linguistic Integrity (rule-based + Ollama fallback)\n  - ✅ A2: Readability Floor (FKGL, FRE, SMOG)\n  - ✅ B1: Thesis Clarity (claim extraction)\n  - ✅ B2: Logical Flow (transition detection)\n  - ✅ B3: Structural Completeness (hook→development→landing)\n  - ✅ C1: Evidence Quality (evidence type detection)\n  - ✅ E1: Platform Reach Potential (LinkedIn optimization)\n- Pipeline includes format detection, weighted aggregation, priority queue, JSON/narrative output\n\n### What's Left\n- **Phase 2**: C2 (Argumentative Rigor), C3 (Proportionality), D2 (Tone Consistency), D3 (Emotional Calibration)\n- **Phase 3**: D1 (Authorial Voice), E2 (Authenticity Signal), E3 (Closing Strength)\n\n### Key Files\n- CLI entry: `tinyqe/tinyqe.py`\n- Analyzers: `tinyqe/analyzers/` (7 built, 5 to go)\n- Format profiles: `tinyqe/config/format_profiles/linkedin.json` (others to create)\n- Core modules: `tinyqe/core/` (format_detector, aggregator, formatter)\n\n### Next Steps for Nemotron\nFollow pattern in existing analyzers to implement remaining 5 dimensions, add to DIMENSIONS list in tinyqe.py, test with LinkedIn/X/blog content.\n\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 28th, 2026 — 12:32 AM (Africa/Johannesburg)## Heartbeat Check (2026-03-28 00:32 GMT+2)\n- Memory files updated: memory/2026-03-28.md (durable), MEMORY.md (long-term TinyQE summary)\n- No active assignments beyond completed TinyQE work\n- No backups requested or needed\n- No weather, calendar, or email checks required per heartbeat interval (inactive state)\n- All TinyQE deliverables completed: brief, framework, 7/12 analyzers prototype\n\n## TinyQE Completion Update (2026-03-28 00:46 GMT+2)\n\n### 🎉 TinyQE Fully Implemented - All 12 Analyzers Complete\n\n**What's Now Complete:**\n- ✅ **All 12 analyzers implemented and tested** (12/12):\n  - A1: Linguistic Integrity (rule-based + Ollama fallback for contextual grammar)\n  - A2: Readability Floor (FKGL, FRE, SMOG vs format benchmarks)\n  - B1: Thesis Clarity (claim extraction from opening/closing)\n  - B2: Logical Flow (transition word/sentence structure detection)\n  - B3: Structural Completeness (hook→development→landing for short-form)\n  - C1: Evidence Quality (evidence type detection via regex patterns)\n  - C2: Argumentative Rigor (fallacy detection, claim-evidence-reasoning structure)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"## TinyQE Progress (2026-03-28)\n\nBuilt strategic brief, framework, and working prototype for TinyQE content evaluation tool:\n\n### What's Complete\n- **Strategic Brief**: `tinyqe/TinyQE_Nemotron_Brief.md` - defines TinyQE purpose, 12-dimension model, format profiles, output design, anti-patterns\n- **Implementation Framework**: `tinyqe/TinyQE_Nemotron_Framework.md` - technical blueprint with architecture, module specs, scoring logic, file structure\n- **Working Prototype**: 7/12 analyzers implemented with full pipeline:\n  - ✅ A1: Linguistic Integrity (rule-based + Ollama fallback)\n  - ✅ A2: Readability Floor (FKGL, FRE, SMOG)\n  - ✅ B1: Thesis Clarity (claim extraction)\n  - ✅ B2: Logical Flow (transition detection)\n  - ✅ B3: Structural Completeness (hook→development→landing)\n  - ✅ C1: Evidence Quality (evi